        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1814427857" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2212438440260211380">This is the funniest of the Zuckerman Unbound tetrology and a fantastic read. Again, Nathan is living in the aftermath of the publication and scandal surrounding his book Carnovsky (Portnoy&apos;s Complaint in Roth&apos;s real life). He is in constant physical pain with 4, then 5, mistresses and decides to drop writing and go to medical school in Chicago. In Chicago, his female limo driver Ricky is treated to his impersonation of a literary rival who Nathan transforms into a pornographer. This is a wonder</span>
  <span id="freeText2212438440260211380" style="display:none">This is the funniest of the Zuckerman Unbound tetrology and a fantastic read. Again, Nathan is living in the aftermath of the publication and scandal surrounding his book Carnovsky (Portnoy's Complaint in Roth's real life). He is in constant physical pain with 4, then 5, mistresses and decides to drop writing and go to medical school in Chicago. In Chicago, his female limo driver Ricky is treated to his impersonation of a literary rival who Nathan transforms into a pornographer. This is a wonderfully funny book fully of life and typical Roth self-deprecation and now one of my favorites from him. Now, I need to read Patrimony.<br />RIP (1933-2018). One of America's literary giants has left us.</span>
